		"name": "Email API Service",
		"description": "Postman collection for Lambda Email API Service deployed on AWS API Gateway.\n\n**Base URL**: {{base_url}}\n**Production URL**: https://futbzxg5x8.execute-api.us-east-1.amazonaws.com\n**Local Development**: http://localhost:8080\n\n**Authentication**:\n- Root and health check endpoints: No authentication required\n- All /email/* endpoints: X-API-Key header required\n- Email pattern endpoints (/email-patterns/*): No authentication required\n- API Key: Set {{api_key}} in environment variables (do not hardcode)\n\n## API Structure\n- **Health Check & Root**: Service status endpoints (no auth)\n- **Email Finder**: 3 endpoints (finder, finder/bulk, single find+verify)\n- **Email Verification**: 4 endpoints (verifier, verifier/single, bulk/verifier, single/verifier)\n- **Email Patterns**: 2 endpoints (add, add/bulk) - no auth required\n\n## Features\n- Find emails by contact name and company domain using Connectra VQL\n- Generate email pattern combinations\n- Verify emails using multiple providers (Truelist, IcyPeas)\n- Bulk email verification (up to 10,000 emails)\n- Single email verification\n- Pattern-based email generation and verification\n- Store and learn email format patterns per company/domain\n\n## Usage\n1. Set environment variables: `base_url`, `api_key`\n2. Test health endpoint first (no auth required)\n3. Find emails using POST /email/finder/ with JSON body\n4. Verify single emails using POST /email/single/verifier/\n5. Verify multiple emails using POST /email/bulk/verifier/\n6. Generate and verify email patterns using POST /email/verifier/\n7. Add email patterns using POST /email-patterns/add (no auth)",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
		"_exporter_id": "20572666"
	},
